<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-05-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-05-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="1045" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1045">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 125.8273/72c.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the <gloss type="to">Brazilian Minister at Mexico
                                        City</gloss>.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-05-22">
                                        <hi rend="italic">May 22, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>74. Your May 22 received. I beg to express the sincere thanks and
                                appreciation of this Government for your untiring efforts in behalf
                                of Vice Consul Silliman at Saltillo. The American people will be
                                highly gratified to learn of his release.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">W. J. Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>